In article <ou8dsINNii9@agate.berkeley.edu>, jbuck@forney (Joe Buck) writes:
[ patent for public key cryptography ]
>We're SOL, I'm afraid.  And once the US and Europe stop fighting about
>agriculture subsidies and they sign the new GATT treaty (General Agreement
>on Tariffs and Trade) the whole world will be SOL, since everyone will
>then need to increase the scope of patent law to include all kinds of
>ridiculous software patents.  It seems that few are aware of the patent
>law bomb that the draft GATT treaty contains that forces all its signers
>to modify their patent laws.

